The paper discusses the use of computer vision techniques to classify species in camera trap images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of transfer learning, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenge of classifying species in new regions, which could involve information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques to gather and analyze data about the new region.
